    systemType:
      "Research-ethics law and committee system with parallel public case-file routes for GRU misconduct statements, NEM medical-health ethics appeals, REK register/postjournal visibility and local institutional handling.",
    summary:
      "Norway is better described as a statutory research-ethics system than as one single research-integrity system. The Research Ethics Act, national committees, domain-specific guidelines, institutional duties, and the misconduct commission together form the core. The case-file pass shows a parallel-route transparency model: GRU publishes full public misconduct statements, NEM publishes a structured database of medical-health ethics appeal decisions, REK exposes project-register and postjournal visibility rather than misconduct case files, and institutions handle first-instance misconduct locally with procedure pages, annual-report traces and public access after finalisation rather than one complete proactive local archive.",
