      "NEM's medical-health appeal database is a second strong public case-file source, but it belongs to the REK/NEM ethics-approval boundary lane rather than the general misconduct lane.",
      "REK project-register and postjournal visibility provide regulatory transparency and access-request routes, not research-misconduct case files.",
      "Empirical surveys, audits, annual reports, books, and anthologies can be evidence sources, not just background literature."
