      "Albania should currently be mapped as a distributed institutional system rather than as a single national research-misconduct board. Law No. 80/2015 on higher education and scientific research creates the national frame, requires institutional ethics councils in higher education institutions, and leaves research activity to institutional statutes and regulations. NASRI/AKKSHI is the national science-funding and monitoring route and hosts a research-and-publication ethics regulation that requires institutions to maintain research-ethics procedures, complaint handling, plagiarism controls, data safeguards, authorship rules and conflict-of-interest management. ASCAL and the Accreditation Board publish a visible quality-assurance decision corridor, but that lane is accreditation and monitoring rather than general misconduct adjudication. Public case visibility remains low: University of Medicine, Tirana gives aggregate Ethics Council activity in its 2023-2024 annual report, while University of Tirana, UAMD and University of Elbasan expose committees, codes and procedures without a public decision archive located in this pass.",
