    summary:
      "Czechia should be mapped as a distributed framework-and-network system rather than as a single national misconduct-office model. The 2005 Ethical Framework of Research and Government Resolution No. 1005 pushed ministries, central bodies, the Czech Academy of Sciences and higher education institutions to create or update local ethics codes. The RDI Council, Act No. 130/2002, Methodology 2017+, the Higher Education Act and the new Act No. 328/2025 create the governance frame. CAS provides the clearest public integrity architecture through its Statutes, Scientific Integrity Committee, 2024 researcher code, 2025 ombuds route and 2024 Open Science Principles. Universities run local codes, ethics commissions, research ethics committees and ombuds routes, while GA CR, TA CR and AZV CR add funder-side conditions and health-research ethics requirements. The committee-and-case-file pass adds one important transparency fragment: Charles University publishes a live Ethics Commission statements and minutes archive, while the CAS and funder lanes remain mostly route-visible rather than case-output archives.",
