    dataSignals: [
      "The local Latvia folder had Overview Latvia.docx as its main local synthesis; the 24 April 2026 case-file pass adds source notes and anchors the update in official public pages.",
      "Latvia's national middle layer is spread across law, academy, council, information systems, policy, and institutional commissions rather than one visible national misconduct board.",
      "The Code of Ethics for Scientists is a strong national norm: it covers human research, data protection, authorship, plagiarism, reviewing, expertise, conflicts of interest and scientific discussion, and it calls for a joint LAS/LCS Scientists' Ethics Committee.",
      "No current LAS/LCS national case-output archive was located in this pass, although academy-journal material and older traces help document the code and ethics-route history.",
      "University of Latvia's Latvian-language Academic Ethics Commission page is the clearest public case-file fragment: it lists decisions from 2019 through 2026 and includes a 7 January 2025 co-authorship breach decision.",
      "University documents split research ethics, academic ethics, academic integrity, publication ethics, plagiarism and ombuds-like complaint routes into distinct bodies and procedures.",
      "Biomedical ethics is not one route: CMEC, RSU REC, ZVA, clinical-trial ethics committees, Genome Research Council and hospital scientific-institution permissions form a multi-route boundary system.",
      "Open science, AI-use guidance, data management, NRIS and international evaluation are unusually visible integrity-adjacent layers."
    ],
