      "Law-activated institutional ethics and deontology model with GSRI and NCRTI strategy, HFRI funding controls, the National Commission for Bioethics and Technoethics as advisory layer, and distributed university and research-centre handling.",
    summary:
      "Greece should not be coded as a single national misconduct-board country. Law 4521/2018 created mandatory research ethics and deontology committees in public research bodies and Law 4957/2022 refreshed the university ethics framework, but the practical system remains distributed: GSRI and NCRTI set strategy, HFRI uses grant conditions to police integrity and ethics compliance, the National Commission for Bioethics and Technoethics issues national recommendations, and most visible operational review or complaint handling sits with institutional EHDE, REC, ethics-committee or integrity-office routes. The 23 April 2026 committee-and-case-file pass did not identify a general public misconduct archive, but it did find official activity-count and report lanes at NKUA and the University of Macedonia, explicit complaint and appeal rules at Thessaly and HMU, confidential allegation handling at IMBB/FORTH, and a much stronger boundary case trail through EOF's National Ethics Committee approval lists, CTIS notices and GCP inspection procedure. Clinical trials, animal research, personal-data supervision, IP and disciplinary rules, and European integrity networks therefore remain adjacent layers rather than one merged national route.",
