    systemType:
      "Legally anchored matrix with the 2018 system law, PAN's Committee on Ethics in Science as a national opinion authority with special procedural weight, institution-led disciplinary and ethics routes, strong NCN-centered funder enforcement, and POL-on/JSA infrastructure plus specialist clinical, animal and data regimes.",
    summary:
      "Poland should not be coded as a single national misconduct-board country. The 2018 Law on Higher Education and Science creates a legally dense environment in which disciplinary commissions, ombudspersons, universities, PAN institutes, research institutes and funders all matter. The strongest national ethics route sits at the Committee on Ethics in Science of the Polish Academy of Sciences PAN, whose opinions have special legal weight in disciplinary adjudication and whose ethics page, annual reports, plenary notes and statements create a real national case-trace lane. That lane is still aggregate or anonymized rather than a searchable archive, but it is stronger than a rules-only publication model. Actual first-line handling still remains local through university disciplinary structures, research ethics committees, bioethics committees and institute-level support routes. Ministerial disciplinary ombuds and commissions form a central statutory route for selected proceedings and appeals, even though no public decision archive was identified for them in this pass. At the same time, NCN builds an unusually strong funder-side compliance system through its code, investigation procedure, ethics guidelines and Research Integrity Committee, while POL-on, the national repository of theses and the Uniform Anti-plagiarism System provide a real digital infrastructure layer. Clinical-trial bioethics, animal research and data protection remain separate but important governance regimes.",
