    summary:
      "Bulgaria is best read as a formal, administrative, and ministerially organized landscape rather than a single case-law style integrity system. The visible core lies in the Academic Staff Act and the ministerial Academic Ethics Committee, surrounded by higher-education law, research and innovation law, NEAA accreditation and ethics controls, NACID registers, BNSF funding and expert-commission rules, BPOS open-science deposit infrastructure, BAS-wide and institute codes, institutional ethics commissions, and separate clinical/biomedical ethics structures. The case-file pass found route density and some institutional annual-report case summaries, but no verified national public misconduct-decision archive.",
