    systemType:
      "Dual legal integrity model combining ministry-led scientific-research governance under the 2025 research law with a separate higher-education academic-integrity regime under the 2019 Law on Academic Integrity, the 2025 Law on Higher Education, a national Ethics Committee, institutional committees, and AKOKVO accreditation controls.",
    summary:
      "Montenegro should not be coded as one uniform national misconduct-board system. The official material points instead to two linked but distinct lanes. Scientific research activity is governed through the Ministry of Education, Science and Innovation, the 2025 Law on Scientific Research Activity, a council, licensing and register tools, strategic planning and open-science policy. Academic integrity in higher education is regulated separately through the 2019 Law on Academic Integrity and the 2025 Law on Higher Education, which anchor a national Ethics Committee, mandatory institutional ethics committees, institutional codes and procedures, and AKOKVO's accreditation and reaccreditation standards. The strongest national ethics body is real and active, and its public trace is stronger than a few isolated news items because the current committee page, annual reports, session posts and an archived 2020 decisions page together form a recurring publication stream. Even so, most concrete first-line case handling still appears to begin and often remain at institutional level. University of Montenegro, Mediterranean University and University of Donja Gorica make that local execution visible, while CInMED, animal-welfare law, personal-data supervision and copyright or IP rules remain important boundary regimes.",
