    summary:
      "San Marino should now be represented as a compact research-integrity system rather than a data-folder-only gap. The practical core is the Universita degli Studi della Repubblica di San Marino (UniRSM): Law No. 69/2023 and Delegated Decree No. 169/2023 create the higher-education frame, UniRSM's Code of Ethics sets integrity, IP and conflict-of-interest standards, and the 2026 Collegio di Disciplina regulation defines a professor and researcher disciplinary route whose sanction or archiving decision is expressly not made public. Biomedical and clinical research is handled separately through the Comitato Sammarinese di Bioetica (CSB), the Comitato Etico per la Ricerca e la Sperimentazione (CERS), the health authority and a visible forms/documents/opinions corridor. Data-protection decisions, USBM innovation and IP sources, the animal-experimentation ban and the general freedom-of-science rule are important boundaries. No national general misconduct board, public UniRSM misconduct archive, or public CERS clinical-study approval register was located in this first pass.",
